  "text": "The rest of the paper is structured as follows. In Section II the models of the DC microgrid and of the attack are presented and the attack-detection problem is formulated. In Section III, we briefly recall the distributed estimation technique and detection strategy presented in [CITATION_1] , and its limitations for DC microgrids are higlighted. In Section IV, the monitoring architecture is sketched, unknown input observers are designed to estimate the state of the neighbors, hence a detection threshold is designed and attack detectability is analyzed. In order to validate the proposed technique, in Section V, simulation results are provided showing the effectiveness of the proposed technique.",
